The paper discusses privacy-preserving strategies and design techniques for open data markets, which are related to data security and privacy (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on the collection and exchange of data, which falls under the category of databases (cs.DB). The use of data to generate business value and personalized services involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper addresses the challenges of ensuring privacy for stakeholders, which is related to social and information networks (cs.SI).
